How would you fix the god function anti-pattern in this YAML printer code?

// src/language-yaml/printer-yaml.js:39
// genericPrint handles ALL YAML node types in one 120+ line function
function genericPrint(path, options, print) {
  const node = path.getValue();
  if (node.type === 'mapping') { /* 20 lines */ }
  else if (node.type === 'sequence') { /* 15 lines */ }
  else if (node.type === 'scalar') { /* 10 lines */ }
  // ... 7 more node types, deeply nested
}

output:
Apply the Strategy pattern to decompose the god function into per-node-type handlers:

```javascript
// 1. Create a registry of node-type printers
const yamlPrinters = {
  mapping: printMapping,
  sequence: printSequence,
  scalar: printScalar,
  comment: printComment,
  anchor: printAnchor,
  tag: printTag,
  directive: printDirective,
};

// 2. Thin dispatcher replaces the god function
function genericPrint(path, options, print) {
  const node = path.getValue();
  const printer = yamlPrinters[node.type];
  if (!printer) {
    throw new Error(`Unknown YAML node type: ${node.type}`);
  }
  return printer(path, options, print);
}

// 3. Each handler is independently testable
function printMapping(path, options, print) {
  // mapping-specific logic only
}
```

Benefits: testability (unit test each handler independently), readability (one concern per function), extensibility (add new node types by adding to the registry, not editing a switch), and reduced merge conflicts.

